The paper deals with a machine learning problem of ranking items based on partially revealed preferences in an adversarial setting. The problem involves pairwise comparisons and statistical modeling, which are common in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the sample size required for reliable identification of the top-K items, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
